rComments: Helga Is a fantastic "teacher". She does not simply get you to read from textbook or learn on your own, but rather she guides you towards actually learning. Unbelievable enthusiasm for Italian language and culture. The course is completely in Italian. There are English and French explanations often, but at least for 1911, it was daunting, but good.

THE BEST TEACHER , she is so caring and truly a representation of an italian women,. She cares about her students deeply and will do anything to help them. She is simply amaizing if u wanna learn any language learn italian with her. She is funny, interactive and just the best time. Never in my whole 4 years at uottawa did i look forward to attendin

One of the best teacher's I've ever had. Loved going to class every week, she made the lectures a lot of fun. 10 out of 10, I would recommend this teacher to anyone who wants an easy going fun class with a great chance to get a good grade.

sweetest prof, super animated and excited. no discussion groups so watching ed puzzle lectures is a bit annoying but not Helgas fault. definitely take her class over the other prof who teaches italian she's much kinder with participation grades and just during the lecutres in general. language angels is cool part of her class as well

She puts an insane level of care into her lectures and makes you really want to learn the language. By far the best language professor at the university. She makes an effort to get to know each and every one of her students and treats them all both with respect and as a friend.

Straight up the best language professor at uOttawa. She is so kind and caring, and she really wants you to enjoy her lectures. Super easy way to learn a new language because she makes it so enjoyable. In 1912, you're even paired up with a student in Italy to practice talking to. Overall amazing class and professor.

H. Paschetto is by far my favorite professor! She is sweet and extremely talented at teaching languages in a way that not only makes sense, but is fun too! I love her classes, and would definitely recommend her if you want to pick up a new language!

Such a kindhearted soul who is really passionate about teaching. She adjusted as best as she could with everything being online and she always had a lot of energy and a big smile in class. She was never pushy or rude and she really wanted her students to do well. I'm glad I took a class with her and I would recommend taking any class with her!
She's such a sweetie! She did a good job adjusting to online school and makes class as fun as she possibly can. She's very kind and understanding and I'm glad I took this class! Grazie!

Honestly the best prof I have had in all my undergrad! She always makes sure her lectures are entertaining even if it's just grammar. She really cares about her students and wants everyone to succeed. The quizzes are super fair and she tells you in advance what you have to study. If you can take a class with Helga, do it!!

She's one of my favourites. Very kind, genuinely cares about her students and their wellbeing. Because of my work schedule, she allowed me to skip tuesday lectures as long as we met once a week for office hour to compensate. The way her "DGDs" were made were amazing, on EdPuzzle (check it out), it was fun and easy to follow. Quizzes are also easy.
She was an amazing teacher, so entertaining!
wow Just an amazing italian teacher ! the kindest teacher iv seen during university !

Helga is the best language teacher I've ever had! She's a very kind person who genuinely cares for her students and her passion for teaching is palpable! She's really funny and her humour makes the 2.5-hour class fly by! Helga feels like more like a friend than a professor and her enthusiasm is contagious! An unbelievable human being and pedagogue!

A great prof who makes lectures fun and engaging! Hands down the best prof and class I've taken so far. I will definitely take another class with her. She's very enthusiastic, she cares about students and wants everyone to do well.
Absolute gem of a prof. and I absolutely loved going to class and the DGD.
She's so funny and personable - and really cares about every student. I've taken a few courses with her and have absolutely loved every one.

I can't think of a better professor, PERIOD! Super engaging, beyond helpful; she makes our two and a half hour DGD go by in a flash! She feels less like a teacher and more like a good friend, and she really takes care to see each and every one of her students succeed. I would probably die for her tbh
She is THE best teacher I've ever had. I am so happy to know her, she's really one of a kind.

This was my first course I took that the prof was so engaging that even the quiet kids were talking everyday. She brings an enthusiasm to her lectures that is contagious, very good lectures and she cares for every person in class and will know your name by the second or third lecture. 10/10 recommend this class even if it's not for credit

Helga is truly one of the sweetest and most caring profs at UOtawa. She is very knowledgeable in Italian and does a great job explaining the content in full. She makes a lot of funny comments throughout her lecture which makes the class time fly by. She is always available for office hours and she will go the extra step. Highly Recommended prof!

Helga is like having a friend who just wants to help you learn Italian. She does everything possible to set her students up for success, she just wants us to learn! Do the assignments, go to class, and just enjoy learning Italian. Shell make it fun :)
Helga is super funny and really cares about making sure you learn Italian the best way possible. She really takes the time to explain things and cuts stuff that she knows is too difficult.

such an amazing person, an amazing teacher, so friendly, nice and funny really helped in the DGDs for understanding verb tenses and other concepts would definitely take another class, she is probably the only reason i was able to pass italian class haha

shes so incredible, very good teacher, hilarious, nice person, she has sweet exemples for us to understand, she wants our success, she loves mangas, animes and Japan, she definitely made my year ! id absolutely and definitely take another class with her
shes incredible, very good teacher, hilarious, kind, she has sweet exemple, she loves mangas, animes and span, she definitely made my year !

Helga is definitely one of the best teachers I've had so far. She really goes the extra mile for you when you need help. Personality wise, she's very caring and hilarious. She's very organized, reminds you of deadlines, helps you out for assignments, etc. Definitely taking Italian classes with her again!
Shes the best linguistics teacher at UOttawa. She really cares about her students, shes super clear and really wants us to pass and get great grades. I will take it again for sure!!

Amazing professor. She is kind, caring, funny, entertaining, and wants you to succeed. It is so reassuring being in her class as she truly cares about her students learning and well-being. She is an excellent lecturer who explains complex subjects well so that you can understand them for tests and exams. You will learn lots in her class.
